Under optimal conditions, in the presence of AA with different concentrations, the blue and yellow fluorescence of CuO-OPD-AA system increases and decreases gradually, respectively (Fig. 4
                        a). As shown in Fig. 4b, the ratio values of I435/I565 are directly proportional to AA concentrations, and the linear range is 1 to 150 μM with determination coefficient of 0.9967. F test was applied for further assessing linearity according to the standard of the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC) [46]. The experimental F value (2.0) is lower than tabulated critical F (3.23), which proves that the constructed linear regression model is reliable. The limit of detection calculated based on 3 times of standard deviation of the blank signal (S/N = 3) is 0.16 μM for AA. According to the calculation method recommended by the modern IUPAC [46], the limit of detection and limit of quantification is 0.34 μM and 1.0 μM, respectively. Compared with the previous reported methods on the AA detection, the proposed method in this experiment is comparable and even more sensitive (Table 1
                        ) [45,47–57]. Furthermore, the designed detection method also possesses the advantage of high accuracy due to the ratiometric fluorescence change.
